  "analyst_notes": "NTPC is the world's most carbon-intensive major utility with 353 MtCO2e Scope 1 emissions. Despite strong domestic credit ratings (AAA) reflecting sovereign backing and regulated tariff model, the company faces severe transition risk. Key concerns: (1) No company-level net-zero commitment - only aspirational India 2070 alignment; (2) No SBTi submission; (3) No CDP Climate disclosure; (4) 30 GW new coal planned by 2032 despite 60 GW RE target; (5) WBA assessment shows expected emissions nearly double the aligned carbon budget. Positive developments: FY25 capacity additions were 83% RE; clean CAPEX estimated at 57-64% of long-term investment plan; strong OCF of INR 50,436 Cr supports aggressive CAPEX program. B5 marginally fails due to elevated Debt/EBITDA (4.6x) and weak Current Ratio (0.92x). B4 fails despite clean CAPEX potentially exceeding 50% threshold because RE share remains below 30% and no net-zero/SBTi commitment exists."
}
